==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jacamar
<hw>Jac"a*mar`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>jacamar</ets>, Braz. <ets>jacamarica</ets>; cf. Sp.
<ets>jacamar</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous
species of tropical American birds of the genus <gen>Galbula</gen> and
allied genera. They are allied to the kingfishers, but climb on tree
trunks like nuthatches, and feed upon insects. Their colors are often
brilliant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jacana</ent>⟦br⟧
